      <p class="kalpana-body">Born in Karnal, India in 1962, Kalpana Chawla became the first woman of Indian origin to travel to space. A mission specialist and robotic arm operator, she flew aboard the Space Shuttle Columbia and logged over 376 hours in space across two missions. Her work in computational fluid dynamics and her relentless pursuit of aerospace excellence made her a role model for millions around the world.</p>
