        <h2 class="section-title">The <span>Sun</span></h2>
        <div class="section-divider"></div>
        <p class="sun-desc">The Sun is the gravitational anchor of our solar system — a massive ball of hot plasma held together by its own gravity. It accounts for 99.86% of the total mass of the solar system and has been fusing hydrogen into helium for roughly 4.6 billion years.</p>
        <p class="sun-desc">Every second, the Sun converts 600 million tonnes of hydrogen into helium via nuclear fusion, releasing energy that takes up to 100,000 years to travel from the core to the surface — and only 8 minutes to reach Earth.</p>
        <div class="sun-fact-grid">
          <div class="sun-fact-cell"><span class="sfc-label">Distance from Earth</span><span class="sfc-value">149.6 M km</span></div>
