        <p class="section-label">Earth's Natural Satellite · Luna</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">The <span>Moon</span></h2>
        <div class="section-divider"></div>
        <p class="sun-desc" style="color:rgba(200,224,255,0.6)">The Moon is Earth's only natural satellite and the fifth largest moon in the solar system. It stabilises Earth's axial tilt, drives ocean tides, and was the first celestial body beyond Earth visited by humans — a feat achieved on July 20, 1969 during Apollo 11.</p>
        <p class="sun-desc" style="color:rgba(200,224,255,0.6)">The Moon is slowly drifting away from Earth at 3.8 cm per year. It is tidally locked — the same face always points toward Earth. Its surface is covered in regolith (fine dust and rock) shaped by billions of years of asteroid impacts.</p>
